@@TJvAlarms
<TITLEIMG TJvAlarms>
#JVCLInfo
<GROUP JVCL.System.AlarmsAndTimers.Alarms>
<FLAG Component>
Summary
  Programmable timer.
Description
  TJvAlarm is a non-visible component that provides you with a programmable timer. The component
  allows multiple alarms to be added, each of which can be set to repeat at a specified interval or
  not at all.
  
  To add scheduled tasks to you application you should:
  
  * Drop a TJvAlarms on a form or data module.
  * Write a handler for the <LINK TJvAlarms.OnAlarm, OnAlarm> event.
  * Set the Active property to True.
  * Add tasks to the component using the Add method in run time or the Alarms property editor in
  design   time.

